aspace_helpers.title: re-think barcodes component of aspace2alma integration based on new knowledge about Analytics

comments.body:
Alma information on currency of Analytics data:

> Data available as of: 10/18/2023 24:15:59 EDT
> Data updated as of: 10/17/2023 20:05:00 EDT

@mzelesky and I interpret this to mean that the data reflects the status of 10/17 at 8pm, and is made available to Analytics circa 4 hours later, on 10/18 shortly after midnight at 12:15am.

Therefore, scheduling the barcodes job for 1am should be safe for aspace2alma.

figgy.title: Use Selenium Standalone instead of Webdrivers

comments.body:
The latest update makes the tests pass in headless mode. But with RUN_IN_BROWSER=true I get the following error (again, potentially correlated with tests where `js: true`)

```
Failure/Error: Unable to find [remote server] org.openqa.selenium.grid.node.config.DriverServiceSessionFactory(DriverServiceSessionFactory.java) to read failed line
          
          Selenium::WebDriver::Error::SessionNotCreatedError:
            Could not start a new session. Error while creating session with the driver service. Stopping driver service: Could not start a new session. Response code 500. Message: unknown error: Chrome failed to start: exited abnormally.
              (unknown error: DevToolsActivePort file doesn't exist)
              (The process started from chrome location /usr/bin/chromium is no longer running, so ChromeDriver is assuming that Chrome has crashed.) 
```
Are you on apple silicon? I wonder if the XVFB stuff on the non-apple docker image has problems

ran the tests in parallel. I had a handful of failures like this 

```
    1.1) Failure/Error: visit user_cas_omniauth_authorize_path                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                         
          Selenium::WebDriver::Error::ServerError:                                                                                                                                       
            status code 404                                                                                                                                                              
          # ./spec/support/features/session_helpers.rb:13:in `sign_in'                                                                                                                             # ./spec/features/numismatic_reference_spec.rb:11:in `block (2 levels) in <top (required)>'    
```

They all passed when I ran a follow-up `rspec --only-failures`

a few other failures I have related to cogeo-mosaic seem unrelated to this PR.

I'm not sure I consider this blocking at this point. maybe it's good enough.
I ran in parallel again and didn't have any of those 404 failures.
